00:13:59.302 --> 00:14:00.363
well-being of his flock.

00:14:01.726 --> 00:14:04.668
If man is to be governed by another

00:14:04.707 --> 00:14:08.909
man rather than be guided directly by God,

00:14:09.649 --> 00:14:13.611
we are best served being led by a

00:14:13.851 --> 00:14:16.753
considerate individual with the mindset of

00:14:16.793 --> 00:14:17.153
a shepherd.

00:14:17.173 --> 00:14:19.413
That's God's take on it.

00:14:20.894 --> 00:14:21.754
Also interesting,

00:14:21.955 --> 00:14:26.135
the last of Yshay's sons would become,

00:14:26.235 --> 00:14:28.557
I should say, Yahowah's Bakowr,

00:14:29.357 --> 00:14:30.258
his firstborn son.

00:14:31.374 --> 00:14:34.436
There are some interesting overtures in

00:14:34.655 --> 00:14:35.576
this decision,

00:14:35.635 --> 00:14:38.758
which reverberate with the fact that the

00:14:38.817 --> 00:14:42.480
covenant began with Abraham's secondborn,

00:14:43.100 --> 00:14:46.322
